From: Arnaud Rebillout <arnaudr@kali.org>
Date: Mon, 25 Aug 2025 22:36:15 +0700
Subject: Add -fpermissive to CFLAGS

GCC-14 requires new CFLAGS:
* -Wno-error=implicit-function-declaration
* -Wno-error=implicit-int

GCC-15 requires another:
* -Wno-error=incompatible-pointer-types

For simplicity, just use `-fpermissive`.
---
 Makefile | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
index d16f45e..f53584b 100755
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -15,6 +15,11 @@ BIN = $DESTDIR/usr/bin
 # DFLAGS = -DTEST -DDEBUG
 DFLAGS =
 CFLAGS = -O
+# Make sure the decades-old source code gets compiled with modern GCC
+CFLAGS += -fpermissive
+#CFLAGS += -Wno-error=implicit-function-declaration \
+#	  -Wno-error=implicit-int \
+#	  -Wno-error=incompatible-pointer-types
 XFLAGS = 	# xtra cflags, set by systype targets
 XLIBS =		# xtra libs if necessary?
 # -Bstatic for sunos,  -static for gcc, etc.  You want this, trust me.
